@SG: I read about half way through pisskop's post before my head exploded. My short answer is that he is all over the place and senseless. One point he calls you town but doesn't trust you, then scum meta, then calls thesp null, then the OMGUS vote now.<br>
I personally do not like the vote on Thesp after I asked him about the null read. His reaction and comment to Thesp is the scummiest thing I see on him.<br>
I won't be joining that wagon because of DBK. I find him more scummy and the fact it gets ignored bothers me more.

@SG<br>
<br>
Im not satisfied you disproved my case.  Im just now going to push acase without support.

@DOMO<br>
I have been in many, many games. Many players can tell you that I'm not afraid for confrontation <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" width="15" height="15" alt=";)" title="Wink"> However, you and pisskop have responded many times to eachother now, that I don't even know what you two are arguing about. And that isn't helpful for anyone. Just finish your reads and make one big post about pisskop and I'm fine with it. But right now, it looks like filler to me.<br>
<br>
@pisskop voters<br>
can all of you repeat the reasons why you are voting him? I think I've only seen posts that he's scummy lately.

@Domo<br>
<br>
Either respond with content or blow away.

@sq:<br>
<br>
huh? what are you talking about? I'm not being intentionally misleading. I stated a very clear opinion on why Neil's and DBK's have not posted recently.

@Domo - Pisskop has asked for both a cop and a Vig to target me at varying times today. It's sort of like flattery regardless of his alignment. This does ignore from him that DBK has claimed Vig and he's not even talking to DBK about it directly, just indirectly - also I just flat out potentially called DBK scum, so I don't think DBK's chances to shoot me remotely balance on what pisskop is or isn't saying.<br>
<br>
@Farside - I agree with you it's bad town play, but it's also bad scumplay. At least, y'know, fakeclaim something to try to out a cop or something. Don't just roll over. I'll agree that it's less bad from scum than from town, but...eh. I agree with you about BJC presuming Neil flips scum, which I'll agree is your viewpoint at the moment. Do you agree with me in theory about DBK if Neil flips town?

@domo<br>
<br>
playstyle?  You try waaay too hard to sack me to be scum.I read it genuine.  her, notsomuch.

@DBK - let me put it this way, Discode is 1000% less likely to be Neil's partner than SiX is - slip or no slip (I don't think there's a slip).<br>
<br>
I still want someone to talk out the Pisskop v. SiX angle. To my mind that's the only remaining debate. I know some people seem to suspect Thesp, but I just don't see that one, and suspicion of him seems to require ignoring a lot of yesterday.
